content.title:
BEST OF 2025 #26: Sudan Archives - The BPM (Stones Throw).

I was such a fan of Sudan Archives‚Äô previous LP Natural Brown Prom Queen (a rhythmic and stylistic joy-ride which ended up at No. 2 in my Best Of 2022 roundup), that as the follow-up‚Äôs title and teaser tracks emerged - all pointing towards a more dance-orientated direction - I was a little concerned that The BPM wouldn‚Äôt be quite my tempo. I needn‚Äôt have worried: Brittney Denise Parks - for she is Sudan Archives - once again delivers ridiculous levels of personality, creativity and quality, using her new persona of Gadget Girl (imagine a hyper-sexualised steam-punk Inspector Gadget) to pull from a dizzying number of dance, club and electronic music forms. Virtually every track is given that trademark Sudan Archives avant-pop spin - a globe-spanning genre-blend here, a manipulation of her trusty violin there - to variously cheeky, lusty, disorientating and banging ends. Not the most cohesive listen, perhaps, but I just keep feeling the urge to return to this record: it beckons you back. Very addictive, bags of fun, next-level production throughout. And even if her full crossover moment is still to come, when Parks sings ‚ÄúI‚Äôm the finest, yeah I said it‚Äù, it‚Äôs hard to disagree. #sudanarchives #thebpm #stonesthrow #2025 #dance #electronic #house #avantpop #electronicmusic #weheardwonders #vinyl #records #vinylcommunity #vinylcollection #vinylcollector #vinylnerd #vinyladdict #vinylfiend #vinylporn #bestof2025 #albumsof2025
